n=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ monthly costs raise to 12.95 a month..</span><hr size=1> Heck even if 20% of the people leave in protest (which will NEVER happen) ... Verant still comes out ahead revenue wise and even higher profit since there will be fewer people to support with infrastructure.<br><br>To me though the price hike is no big deal ... playing on Legends <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p>Aiwe yan`Sael <BR> Minstrel of Erollisi Marr <BR>-=Ascending=-<BR>Stormhammer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upurifyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Purifyre</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 3:00:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23018.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> You have to love Verant's procedures for changing to a new subscription rate ( ie I want to go on the 6 month plan now instead of monthly ) - in order to change plans you have to completely cancel your account before you can subscribe to a new one - I wonder how many people are going to cancel, play out their remaining time, then not bother to resubscribe?  If they had an ounce of brains they would allow you to switch automatically at the end of the month when your monthly plan starts its new cycle... Oh wait I forgot, they want to make it as difficult as possible so no-one uses the discount plans... I wanted to switch to the 6 month plan back in June/July of '99 but I don't trust the Billing department - heard too many stories of people cancelling their accounts then resubscribing a few months later to find a stripped account with the only possible suspect being an employee in Billing who &quot;leaked&quot; the username/password for an account they thought would be permanently cancelled... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 3:03:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23018.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ monthly costs raise to 12.95 a month..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> As for the rate hike, I think it's kind of an assinine thing to do. What part of their operating costs have gone up? Why does it cost more per person all of the sudden to run the servers than it has for the last 3 years. I get the feeling they'd just rather have a little more money to work with. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Because each &quot;Server&quot; isn't one server, its a large cluster of numerous servers.  In the last 3 years EQ has greatly increased the number of zones in the game, those zones require servers.  Bandwidth has gotten more costly in the last 3 years.  Labor has gotten more costly.  Do you think those developers haven't received a raise in 3 years?  How many of you would stick around at a job that didn't give you even a small raise every year?  Electric costs in California are a lot higher than 3 years ago.  Taxes, leases, inflation, etc. and so on, there are a lot of things in a business that increase every year.<br><br>They have added a tremendous amount of content to the game in 3 years without an increase.  And no, the $30 you paid for the expansions wasn't an increase.  They make very little on those expansions sold in stores.  Most of that $30 goes to the retailer, distributor, and the producer of the CD, case, and box, as well as the artwork costs, advertisement costs, etc.  If Verant got $1 per expansion CD I wouldn't be surprised, thats what recording artists get per CD.<br><br>Hell with 4% inflation alone they should be charging $11.13 just to be getting the same effective worth.  <br><br>EQ is probably my only bill that hasn't gone up in 3 years.  For those that are saying &quot;thats it, I'm cancelling my account&quot;  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   yeah right, 90% of you won't do it. For those that do, take care, LLFM.<br> <p><table><td><img src="http://members.aol.com/twiggiebrell/jaradissig.jpg"></td><td><TABLE STYLE="filter:GLOW(color=maroon,strength=#+1)"  ><font color=white>Jaradis Stormcaller – Oracle of Winter - Enemy to all of Velious<br>Jaradin Stormcaller - Warlord in Training - Ally of Kael Drakkel<br>Twiggie Tymberwolf - 52nd Wanderer - Friend to Dragon and Dwarves<br>Brell Serilis Server</font></table><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21764">Stats and Gear</a></td></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulifeofbrion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Life of Brion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 3:05:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23018.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ monthly costs raise to 12.95 a month..</span><hr size=1> There's always the 2 year plan fo $190. That's $7.92 a month.<br><